polls.title: Proposal to fix Report system abusal (Reporting all flips/Not reporting all flips)
polls.description: Get the least reported(=best) flips from the previous validation/s and add them to a long session. One or Two for each person. If a person reports this flip, he's considered an abuser of the system and his reports are not counted. Do the same with the worst flips (reuse, show 1 or 2 in long, if person does NOT report them - he is abuser). Pros: it fixes report abuse, doesn't require to create additional flips. Cons: reuses previously seen flips, reducing security (might be ok, since it's going to be only 2-4 flips in the long session)
polls.creator: 0xa1bdc2f3de4908ee464f8695448c3f4390111d26

options.description: Yes, reported flips should count as correct for short session scoring.
No, reported flips should be removed from short session scoring.

polls.title: Should reported flips count as correct during the short session?
polls.description: If a flip is reported, it is removed from the short session scoring for anyone who received it. If a user gets a lot of bad flips in the short session and they are reported, their short session can be reduced to only a few flips. For example, if you received 4 reported flips in the short session, your short session score would be against the 2 remaining flips. To achieve the 60% score requirement in short session, you would be left in a situation where you needed to get both flips right or you would fail. This proposal would make any flips you receive in the short session that were reported count as a correct answer in the short session.
polls.creator: 0x422e2aa5bca28454e8a0bc161e84f306bf764631

options.description: Yes, but needs changes or tweaks

polls.title: Alternate proposal to fix report system
polls.description: Add a DNA reward to the validation session for succesfully reporting a flip. By rewarding people for reporting poor flips, this will encourage reporting. To prevent abuse, limit the number of reports users are given per session (i.e. 3 reports per session). This will force people to use their reports wisely and target the "low-hanging" flips (sequential 1234 flips, flips which do not use either word, pornography). If a user does not receive any bad flips, they will either not use the reports, or they will report randomly which should not result in valid flips being reported succesfully. If a user gets many bad flips, they will target the worst flips. Ideally this will improve flip quality over time, making the bad flips rare, and an easy target for the report reward when they do show up.
polls.creator: 0x422e2aa5bca28454e8a0bc161e84f306bf764631

polls.title: Financial stimulus for flips curation (i.e. reporting bad and only bad flips)
polls.description: For motivating people to take flips curation seriously we can enforce these rules:  If a flip is considered by a committee as a bad one and a member of this committee reported it then he gets a reward, otherwise the person doesn't get any reward. If a flip is considered by a committee as a good one and a member of this committee didn't report it then he gets a reward, otherwise the person doesn't get any reward.
